A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 16-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 criminal trespass, so as to include gatherings for the purposes of religious worship and
3 observance or acknowledging the death of an individual; to provide for related matters; to
4 repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Code Section 16-7-21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to criminal
8 trespass, is amended by adding a new subsection to read as follows:
9 "(f) A person commits the offense of criminal trespass when he or she knowingly and
10 without authority enters and remains upon the land or premises of another person and
11 willfully and maliciously interrupts or disturbs any assembly of people met or convened
12 for purposes of religious worship or observance or for purposes of acknowledging the death
13 of an individual in such a manner that a reasonable person would conclude that the person
14 who commits the act is a threat to the safety of any person so assembled."
